article.title: QinetiQ North America to Provide Computing Systems Support to SEATech
article.author: Henry Kenyon
article.text: The Naval Surface Warfare Command's Carderock Division has awarded QinetiQ North America's Systems Engineering Group a five-year contract to provide high-performance computing systems support to the Ship Engineering and Analysis Technology Center (SEATech) in West Bethesda, Maryland.Â The five-year contract, awarded under the Seaport Enhanced contract vehicle, has a total ceiling value of $4.4 million.
